<p>In a sample, a correlation of 0.64 is found between two variables <em>x</em> and <em>y</em>. The standard deviation of <em>x</em> is 24, and the standard deviation of <em>y</em> is 18.</p>
<p>Calculate the regression coefficient <em>b</em>.</p>
</p>]]></text>
</questiontext>
<generalfeedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
<p>Use the formula on the formula sheet for correlation (Chapter 9).</p>
<p>Filling it in gives <span class="math inline">\(0.64 = \frac{24}{18 \times b}\)</span>. Describe gives <span class="math inline">\(b = 0.64 \times \frac{18}{24} = 0.48\)</span>.</p>
</p>]]></text>
</generalfeedback>
